证据片段: The irradiation growth behavior of annealed polycrystalline Zircaloy-2 has been investigated in the DIDO reactor at Harwell at fluences up to $1 \times 1 0 ^ { 2 5 }$ neutrons $( \mathsf { n } ) \mathsf { m } ^ { - 2 }$ $( E \bar { > } 1 \ \mathbf { M e V } )$ and in the temperature range 513 to 673 K.

证据片段: The irradiation growth behavior of annealed polycrystalline Zircaloy-2 has been investigated in the DIDO reactor at Harwell at fluences up to $1 \times 1 0 ^ { 2 5 }$ neutrons $( \mathsf { n } ) \mathsf { m } ^ { - 2 }$ $( E \bar { > } 1 \ \mathbf { M e V } )$ and in the temperature range 513 to 673 K.

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_026_chunk1
证据片段: Growth strain data for two batches of rolled, annealed Zircaloy plate did not obey the $G \propto ( 1 - 3 f )$ texture relationship with transverse direction specimens $\langle f = 0 . 2 5$ and $\mathnormal { f } = 0 . 3 5 )$ exhibiting negative growth following an initial positive transient.

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_026_chunk1
证据片段: The effect of irradiation temperature on growth was not marked over the range studied except that, at $\yen 73\mathrm { ‰}$ , growth strains appeared to saturate at low fluences.

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_026_chunk1
证据片段: Apart from this, longitudinal and transverse growth strains decreased slightly with increasing temperature above $\$ 73\ 8$ .

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_026_chunk1
证据片段: Specimens of large grained, $\beta$ -annealed Zircaloy with a completely random structure showed virtually no sensitivity of growth to either fluence or temperature under the conditions studied.

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_026_chunk1
证据片段: Previous studies of irradiation growth in annealed Zircaloy [1-5] have shown that the magnitude and direction of growth strains are dependent upon three main variables: crystallographic texture, fast neutron fluence (or displacement damage), and temperature.

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_026_chunk1
证据片段: In fully recrystallized Zircaloy, other variables such as degree of cold work (or dislocation density) and grain shape, which have been shown to be important factors in the irradiation growth of cold-worked Zircaloy and zirconium-niobium alloys [1,3,6], are assumed to be relatively insignificant.
